li_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/session-routing/design.md:\n  Line 95: | `IdentitySecretName` | `\"picod-router-identity\"` |\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/session-routing/spec.md:\n  Line 115: - **THEN** it creates opaque secret `picod-router-identity` in namespace from `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` or `default` with keys `private.pem` and `public.pem`\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/code-execution/design.md:\n  Line 1: # Code Execution (PicoD) — Design (from source)\n  Line 3: Derived from `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/picod` and `cmd/picod` in `/tmp/agentcube-ref`. Field names, types, tags, and constants match the Go definitions.\n  Line 7: - **Main**: `cmd/picod/main.go` — parses flags, constructs `picod.Config`, `picod.NewServer(config)`, `server.Run()`.\n  Line 13: | `-port`    | `int`  | `8080`  | `Port for the PicoD server to listen on` |\n  Line 161: \t\"service\": \"PicoD\",\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/code-execution/spec.md:\n  Line 1: # Code Execution (PicoD) Specification\n  Line 5: PicoD is an HTTP daemon that runs commands inside a configurable workspace jail, manages workspace files, and exposes a health endpoint with JWT (RSA)–protected APIs.\n  Line 147: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 200 with `status` `\"ok\"`, `service` `\"PicoD\"`, `version` `\"0.0.1\"`, and `uptime` as a string from `time.Since(server start)`\n  Line 173: The system SHALL read CLI flags `-port` and `-workspace`, build `picod.Config`, and listen on `\":<port>\"`. If `workspace` is empty, the workspace root SHALL be the current working directory (fatal if `os.Getwd` fails). The HTTP server SHALL use `ReadHeaderTimeout` of 10 seconds.\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/project.md:\n  Line 34:   Sandbox 