{"type":"text","timestamp":1775857869787,"sessionID":"ses_286a23b06ffeA0T03gESJ1w8kY","part":{"id":"prt_d7960940d0015bXSjororgGksX","messageID":"msg_d79607f31001ONI8HYwJw5UnK8","sessionID":"ses_286a23b06ffeA0T03gESJ1w8kY","type":"text","text":"I've written the `proposal.md` for AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API. The proposal includes:\n\n- **Overview**: PicoD as an HTTP daemon for secure command execution and file management\n- **Purpose**: Define the command execution API for PicoD daemon\n- **Scope**: HTTP server core, JWT authentication, command/file/health APIs, path security\n- **Impact Analysis**: Components affected (CodeInterpreter controller, Router, Sandbox orchestration, Helm charts, CI/CD, Python SDK)\n- **Design Decisions**: With rationale for JWT strategy, workspace jail, default timeout, file upload formats, health endpoint auth, default file mode\n- **API Design**: Complete endpoint specifications for execute, upload, list, download, and health\n- **Data Structures**: Config, Request/Response types, AuthManager, Server\n- **Security Considerations**: Authentication, path security, command execution safety, network security\n- **Testing Strategy**: Unit, integration, and coverage targets\n- **Configuration**: CLI flags and environment variables\n- **Migration Strategy**: 4-phase implementation plan (5 weeks)\n- **Future Enhancements**: Streaming, session management, advanced file ops, metrics, key rotation\n\nThe LSP errors shown are pre-existing issues in other files and unrelated to this proposal.","time":{"start":1775857869786,"end":1775857869786}}}
